The paper focuses on detecting malicious banking botnet activities using artificial intelligence techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically mentions the use of deep learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system also leverages Cyber Data Lake, which is a network infrastructure (cs.NI) used for storing and analyzing large amounts of cybersecurity-related data. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation results of the system, which involves testing and measuring the effectiveness of the system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
